SIMPLE: interpret
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interpret
<hw>In*ter"pret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interpreted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Interpreting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>interpr⟦ecir⟧ter</ets>, L. <ets>interpretari</ets>, p. p.
<ets>interpretatus</ets>, fr. <ets>interpres</ets> interpeter, agent,
negotiator; <ets>inter</ets> between + (prob.) the root of
<ets>pretium</ets> price. See <er>Price</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To explain or tell the meaning of; to expound; to
translate orally into intelligible or familiar language or terms; to
decipher; to define; -- applied esp. to language, but also to dreams,
signs, conduct, mysteries, etc.; <as>as, to <ex>interpret</ex> the
Hebrew language to an Englishman; to <ex>interpret</ex> an Indian
speech.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Emmanuel, which being <qex>interpreted</qex> is, God with us.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. i. 23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And Pharaoh told them his dreams; but there was none that could
<qex>interpret</qex> them unto Pharaoh.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xli.
8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To apprehend and represent by means of art; to show
by illustrative representation; <as>as, an actor <ex>interprets</ex> the
character of Hamlet; a musician <ex>interprets</ex> a sonata; an artist
<ex>interprets</ex> a landscape.</as></def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To translate; explain; solve; render; expound;
elucidate; decipher; unfold; unravel.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpret</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interpret
<hw>In*ter"pret</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To act as an
interpreter.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpretable</ent>⟦br⟧
